# jemdoc: menu{MENU}{software.html}
= Hao Zhu --- Software
[https://www.informatik.uni-freiburg.de/ Department of Computer Science], [https://uni-freiburg.de/ University of Freiburg]


Source for most of my recent projects is hosted on [https://github.com/dxogrp this GitHub site] .

Some older software which I was involved (e.g., during my PhD) may still be available under my personal GitHub site [https://github.com/haozhu10015 haozhu10015] and the [https://github.com/nrgrp Neurorobotics Group] GitHub site.

== Recent software

- [https://github.com/dxogrp/dbcp +dbcp+]: a CVXPY extension for biconvex programming
- [https://github.com/dxogrp/cvxgenrust +cvxgenrust+]: a Python package for generating Rust crates from parameterized CVXPY problems.
- [https://github.com/haozhu10015/jemdoc-rs +jemdoc-rs+]: a Rust rewrite of jemdoc\+MathJax for creating websites
- [https://github.com/dxogrp/rlfit +rlfit+]: a Python package for fitting reinforcement learning models to behavior data under multi-armed bandits
- [https://github.com/cvxpy/cvxrust +cvxrust+]: a Rust implementation of disciplined convex programming
- [https://github.com/nrgrp/saferl-lib +saferl-lib+]: a toolkit for constrained reinforcement learning and safe reinforcement learning research
- [https://github.com/dxogrp/dlfm +dlfm+]: a framework for fitting discrete latent factor models in Python
- [https://github.com/haozhu10015/latex-template +latex-template+]: LaTex templates for article, slides, book, and poster

== Not so recent software

- [https://github.com/nrgrp/cvx_irl +cvx_irl+]: for inverse reinforcement learning via convex optimization
- [https://github.com/nrgrp/hiql +hiql+]: for hierarchical inverse Q-learning